:"1505","Ellam Manor, Crayford, London Borough of Bexley, London, England":"Crayford, London, England, United Kingdom","London, Middlesex, England, United Kingdom":"London, England, United Kingdom","Herefordshire, England":"Herefordshire, England","London, England":"London, England"},"nl":{"10 January 1430–10 January 1493":"10 januari 1430–10 januari 1493","1430–1493":"1430–1493","1435–Female":"1435–Overleden","1450–Female":"1450–Overleden","1443–1521":"1443–1521","1457–1505":"1457–1505","1415–1481":"1415–1481","1417–Female":"1417–Overleden","about 1481":"circa 1481","1450":"1450","1493":"1493","1481":"1481","10 January 1493":"10 januari 1493","10 January 1430":"10 januari 1430","1415":"1415","1457":"1457","1435":"1435","1455":"1455","1521":"1521","1443":"1443","1430":"1430","1417":"1417","1505":"1505","Ellam Manor, Crayford, London Borough of Bexley, London, England":"Crayford, London, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","London, Middlesex, England, United Kingdom":"London, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Herefordshire, England":"Herefordshire, England","London, England":"London, England"},"en":{"10 January 1430–10 January 1493":"10 January 1430–10 January 1493","1430–1493":"1430–1493","1435–Female":"1435–Deceased","1450–Female":"1450–Deceased","1443–1521":"1443–1521","1457–1505":"1457–1505","1415–1481":"1415–1481","1417–Female":"1417–Deceased","about 1481":"about 1481","1450":"1450","1493":"1493","1481":"1481","10 January 1493":"10 January 1493","10 January 1430":"10 January 1430","1415":"1415","1457":"1457","1435":"1435","1455":"1455","1521":"1521","1443":"1443","1430":"1430","1417":"1417","1505":"1505","Ellam Manor, Crayford, London Borough of Bexley, London, England":"Crayford, London, England, United Kingdom","London, Middlesex, England, United Kingdom":"London, England, United Kingdom","Herefordshire, England":"Herefordshire, England","London, England":"London, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Ilam,","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from Elam Grange in Bingley (Yorkshire). It is possible that some instances of the modern surname are from Elham in Kent or a lost place called Elham in Crayford (Kent), but the strong association with Yorkshire militates against this. Elam Grange probably means ‘river pool’, from Old English <i>ēa</i> ‘river’ + <i>lum(m)</i> ‘pool’."],"variants":[{"name":"Elem","meanings":["Altered form of English   Elam  ."]}]},{"name":"Mercer","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English and Catalan: occupational name for a merchant, from Old French <i>mercier</i>, <i>merchier</i> (see   Mercier  ). In Middle English the term was applied particularly to someone who dealt in textiles, especially the more costly and luxurious fabrics such as silks, satin, and velvet."],"variants":[{"name":"Mercier","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Armand, Marcel, Andre, Pierre, Gaston, Lucien, Aurele, Jacques, Normand, Laurent, Michel, Valmont.","French and Channel Islands (Jersey): occupational name for a merchant, from Old French <i>mercier</i>, from Late Latin <i>merciarius</i> (an agent derivative of <i>merx</i>, genitive <i>mercis</i> ‘merchandise’). This name was also taken to England by Huguenot refugees. Compare   Marshall   and   Mercy  ."]},{"name":"Marcey","meanings":["English:","variant of   Mercer  , from Middle English <i>mercer</i>, <i>merser</i>, <i>marser</i> ‘textile merchant’, in which final <i>-er</i> has been weakened to <i>-ey</i>.","(of Norman origin): habitational name from Marcy in France (Manche)."]}]},{"name":"Thomas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":24,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"When Thomas Ilam, Mercer was born on 10 January 1430, in Herefordshire, England, his father, John Ellam, was 16 and his mother, Millicent Leigh, was 14. He had at least 1 daughter with Jane Verdun. He died on 10 January 1493, in London, England, at the age of 63."},"et":{"10 January 1430–10 January 1493":"10. jaanuar 1430–10. jaanuar 1493","1430–1493":"1430–1493","1435–Female":"1435–Surnud","1450–Female":"1450–Surnud","1443–1521":"1443–1521","1457–1505":"1457–1505","1415–1481":"1415–1481","1417–Female":"1417–Surnud","about 1481":"umbes 1481","1450":"1450","1493":"1493","1481":"1481","10 January 1493":"10. jaanuar 1493","10 January 1430":"10. jaanuar 1430","1415":"1415","1457":"1457","1435":"1435","1455":"1455","1521":"1521","1443":"1443","1430":"1430","1417":"1417","1505":"1505","Ellam Manor, Crayford, London Borough of Bexley, London, England":"Crayford, London, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","London, Middlesex, England, United Kingdom":"London, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Herefordshire, England":"Herefordshire, England","London, England":"London, England"},"fi":{"10 January 1430–10 January 1493":"10. tammikuuta 1430–10. tammikuuta 1493","1430–1493":"1430–1493","1435–Female":"1435–Kuollut","1450–Female":"14